                    "\"Choice is both a right and a duty, my love. You will understand, in time.\" Volkath whispered in her ear, \"There is no safety in the margin between light and darkness. There is only storm and fury, even if it has yet to rear its head. This is my parting gift for you. You will need it, when the storm comes...\"As he spoke, he lifted Marja's chin and kissed her, a kiss so long that Marja felt out of breath. It was as though she lost something, and gained something at the same time.\n" +
                    "\n" +
